## Community Types

### Global Community (Public Group)
Community created by platform administration.

**Properties:**
- All users are members by default (immediately after registration)
- Per **`MeritResolverService`**, **`fee`** and **`withdrawal`** always resolve to **`GLOBAL_COMMUNITY_ID`** for **any** community (not only priority hubs).
- Priority hub communities (`isPriority` or `typeTag` in `marathon-of-good`, `future-vision`, `team-projects`, `support`) share the global merit wallet for **`voting`**, **`tappalka_reward`**, and **`investment`** as in **Merit** (plus the **`isProject` + `voting`** rule).
- Merits earned in one priority hub can be spent in another priority hub for those **`voting` / `tappalka_reward` / `investment`** contexts (shared **`GLOBAL_COMMUNITY_ID`**); **`fee`** / **`withdrawal`** already use that wallet for everyone.
- User CANNOT leave a global community (priority hubs are not leavable via `leaveLocalCommunity`)
- List of global communities can expand

### Local Community (Private Group)
Community created and managed by users.

**Properties:**
- Non-priority local communities use **that community’s wallet id** for voting/tappalka/investment per **Merit** (not the global wallet), unless `isProject` voting branch applies
- Full set of settings available to lead
- User can be member of ANY number of local communities
- User can be lead of ANY number of communities
- **Leave (code):** `communities.leaveCommunity` → `CommunityService.leaveLocalCommunity`: allowed for **participants** in eligible local communities; **lead** cannot leave (must transfer lead first); **`isProject === true`** must use the project leave flow; **priority** communities cannot be left this way
- Lead CANNOT delete community — only request deletion from administration (dedicated "request deletion" API is not implemented in current codebase)

### Lead
Administrator of a local community (creator or appointed). Has access to community settings.

