## Mechanics

### Tappalka
Mechanism for comparing two posts for merit emission. User sees two posts, chooses better one — chosen post receives merit (emission).

### Emission
Creation of new merits by the system. Happens through tappalka, from administration, or as welcome merits at registration.

**Welcome merits:** Amount from platform setting `welcomeMeritsGlobal` (PlatformSettings); credited to global wallet at registration.

### Stop-Loss
Per-post floor for **rating** when paying **tappalka show cost**: rating is not reduced below **`publication.stopLoss`** (treated as 0 when absent). Eligibility to appear in tappalka pairs also depends on **`tappalkaSettings.minRating`**, **`tappalkaSettings.showCost`**, `investmentPool`, and combined spendable rating (`pool + max(0, score - stopLoss)`) as implemented in **`tappalka.service.ts`** (`getEligiblePosts`). See **@business-tappalka.mdc** for the full rules.

### Investment Pool
Post-level balance funded by investors. Used first for tappalka show-cost deductions when the post has investing fields enabled (`investingEnabled` / pool balance).

### Investment Contract
Immutable agreement created at post publication when investing is enabled. Defines `investorSharePercent` (within community `settings.investorShareMin`..`settings.investorShareMax`) and distribution rules between author and investors.

**In code:** `publication.investorSharePercent`; bounds in `community.settings.investorShareMin` / `investorShareMax`.

**Close distribution toggle:** `community.settings.distributeAllByContractOnClose` — when `true`, on close all merits (pool + rating) are distributed by contract; when `false`, pool is returned to investors proportionally first, then rating by contract (see `community.schema.ts` / `CommunitySettings` comments).

### Investor Share
Portion of withdrawal/close distribution allocated to investors according to contract percent, then split proportionally by each investor's contribution.

### TTL (Time To Live)
Post lifetime limit in days. For investment posts, TTL may be required by community setting `requireTTLForInvestPosts` and capped by `maxTTL`.

**In code:** `publication.ttlDays` (e.g. 7, 14, 30, 60, 90), `publication.ttlExpiresAt`; community: `settings.requireTTLForInvestPosts`, `settings.maxTTL`.

### Inactive Close
Automatic post closing after configured days without earnings (`inactiveCloseDays`).

### Comment (Vote) Withdrawal
Withdrawal from a **comment** score via **`votes.withdrawFromVote`** (`votes.router.ts`). Eligibility uses **`VoteService.canUserWithdraw`** for the target. This path is **not** the same implementation as **`publications.withdraw`** for every edge case (e.g. МД `sourceEntity*` routing). See **@business-content.mdc**.

### noAuthorWalletSpend
Publication-level flag. When true, tappalka does **not** debit the **author’s personal wallet** for show cost after pool and rating; posts with **`sourceEntityId`** may still use the source **`CommunityWallet`** per **@business-tappalka.mdc**. Post exits tappalka when no remaining source can cover the cost.

